pace: pre-wrap; min-width: 1px;">Read More &amp; Download</span><svg viewBox="0 0 32 32" fill="none" xmlns="http://www.w3.org/2000/svg"><circle class="button-primary-circle" cx="16" cy="16" r="16"></circle><path d="M8 16.956h12.604l-3.844 4.106 1.252 1.338L24 16l-5.988-6.4-1.252 1.338 3.844 4.106H8v1.912z" class="color-spacesuit-white"></path></svg></a></div></div></div></div><div class="hds-card-custom hds-card color-carbon-black display-flex flex-column margin-bottom-5 mobile:grid-col-12 tablet:grid-col-6 desktop:grid-col-3 margin-bottom-6"><div class="hds-card-inner"><div class="hds-card-thumbnail hds-card-hover-zoom-image margin-bottom-2 bg-carbon-black"><figure class="hds-media-background  "><img width="1280" height="720" src="https://assets.science.nasa.gov/dynamicimage/assets/science/missions/hubble/multimedia/e-books/Hubble_BlackHolesCover_4StoryBlock.jpg?w=1280&amp;h=720&amp;fit=clip&amp;crop=faces%2Cfocalpoint" class="attachment-large size-large" alt="Hubble Focus: Black Holes e-Book Cover. An illustration of the Hubble Space Telescope with its opening facing the viewer and marking the &quot;o&quot; in Focus. An image of the giant galaxy M87 and its black - generated- jet fills most of the cover." style="transform: scale(1.2); transform-origin: 50% 50%; object-position: 50% 50%; object-fit: cover;" block_context="nasa-block" loading="lazy" decoding="async" srcset="https://assets.science.nasa.gov/dynamicimage/assets/science/missions/hubble/multimedia/e-books/Hubble_BlackHolesCover_4StoryBlock.jpg?w=1280&amp;h=720&amp;fit=crop&amp;crop=faces%2Cfocalpoint 1280w, https://assets.science.nasa.gov/dynamicimage/assets/science/missions/hubble/multimedia/e-books/Hubble_BlackHolesCover_4StoryBlock.jpg?w=300&amp;h=169&amp;fit=crop&amp;crop=faces%2Cfocalpoint 300w, https://assets.science.nasa.gov/dynamicimage/assets/science/missions/hubble/multimedia/e-books/Hubble_BlackHolesCover_4StoryBlock.jpg?w=768&amp;h=432&amp;fit=crop&amp;crop=faces%2Cfocalpoint 768w, https://assets.science.nasa.gov/dynamicimage/assets/science/missions/hubble/multimedia/e-books/Hubble_BlackHolesCover_4StoryBlock.jpg?w=1024&amp;h=576&amp;fit=crop&amp;crop=faces%2Cfocalpoint 1024w, https://assets.science.nasa.gov/dynamicimage/assets/science/missions/hubble/multimedia/e-books/Hubble_BlackHolesCover_4StoryBlock.jpg?w=400&amp;h=225&amp;fit=crop&amp;crop=faces%2Cfocalpoint 400w, https://assets.science.nasa.gov/dynamicimage/assets/science/missions/hubble/multimedia/e-books/Hubble_BlackHolesCover_4StoryBlock.jpg?w=600&amp;h=338&amp;fit=crop&amp;crop=faces%2Cfocalpoint 600w, https://assets.science.nasa.gov/dynamicimage/assets/science/missions/hubble/multimedia/e-books/Hubble_BlackHolesCover_4StoryBlock.jpg?w=900&amp;h=506&amp;fit=crop&amp;crop=faces%2Cfocalpoint 900w, https://assets.science.nasa.gov/dynamicimage/assets/science/missions/hubble/multimedia/e-books/Hubble_BlackHolesCover_4StoryBlock.jpg?w=1200&amp;h=675&amp;fit=crop&amp;crop=faces%2Cfocalpoint 1200w" sizes="auto, (max-width: 1280px) 100vw, 1280px" /></figure></div><div class="padding-right-0"><div class="margin-bottom-1"><h3 class="heading-18">Black Holes: Into the Vortex</h3></div><p class="margin-top-0 line-height-lg"><em>Black Holes: Into the Vortex</em> explores Hubble’s recent discoveries about black holes, incredibly dense objects whose gravity is so intense that not even light can escape its pull.</p><div class="margin-top-2"><a href="https://science.nasa.gov/mission/hubble/multimedia/e-books/hubble-focus-black-holes-into-the-vortex/" target="_self" class="button-primary button-primary-md link-external-false"><span role="textbox" aria-multiline="true" aria-label="Write button text here" class="line-height-alt-1" style="white-space: pre-wrap; min-width: 1px;">Read More &amp; Download</span><svg viewBox="0 0 32 32" fill="none" xmlns="http://www.w3.org/2000/svg"><circle class="button-primary-circle" cx="16" cy="16" r="16"></circle><path d="M8 16.956h12.604l-3.844 4.106 1.252 1.338L24 16l-5.988-6.4-1.252 1.338 3.844 4.106H8v1.912z" class="color-spacesuit-white"></path></svg></a></div></div></div></div>				</div>
