						<div class="card-carousel-slider">
			<div class="hds-card-custom hds-card color-carbon-black display-flex flex-column margin-bottom-5 "><div class="hds-card-inner"><div class="hds-card-thumbnail hds-card-hover-zoom-image margin-bottom-2 bg-carbon-black"><figure class="hds-media-background  "><img width="1024" height="1024" src="https://science.nasa.gov/wp-content/uploads/2023/05/hubble-homepage-hubble-vs-webb-card-1.png?w=1024" class="attachment-large size-large" alt="" style="transform: scale(1); transform-origin: 48% 14%; object-position: 48% 14%; object-fit: cover;" block_context="nasa-block" loading="lazy" decoding="async" srcset="https://science.nasa.gov/wp-content/uploads/2023/05/hubble-homepage-hubble-vs-webb-card-1.png 1041w, https://science.nasa.gov/wp-content/uploads/2023/05/hubble-homepage-hubble-vs-webb-card-1.png?resize=150,150 150w, https://science.nasa.gov/wp-content/uploads/2023/05/hubble-homepage-hubble-vs-webb-card-1.png?resize=300,300 300w, https://science.nasa.gov/wp-content/uploads/2023/05/hubble-homepage-hubble-vs-webb-card-1.png?resize=768,768 768w, https://science.nasa.gov/wp-content/uploads/2023/05/hubble-homepage-hubble-vs-webb-card-1.png?resize=1024,1024 1024w, https://science.nasa.gov/wp-content/uploads/2023/05/hubble-homepage-hubble-vs-webb-card-1.png?resize=50,50 50w, https://science.nasa.gov/wp-content/uploads/2023/05/hubble-homepage-hubble-vs-webb-card-1.png?resize=100,100 100w, https://science.nasa.gov/wp-content/uploads/2023/05/hubble-homepage-hubble-vs-webb-card-1.png?resize=200,200 200w, https://science.nasa.gov/wp-content/uploads/2023/05/hubble-homepage-hubble-vs-webb-card-1.png?resize=400,400 400w, https://science.nasa.gov/wp-content/uploads/2023/05/hubble-homepage-hubble-vs-webb-card-1.png?resize=600,600 600w, https://science.nasa.gov/wp-content/uploads/2023/05/hubble-homepage-hubble-vs-webb-card-1.png?resize=900,900 900w" sizes="auto, (max-width: 1024px) 100vw, 1024px" /></figure></div><div class="padding-right-0"><div class="margin-bottom-1"><h3 class="heading-18">On The Shoulders of a Giant</h3></div><p class="margin-top-0 line-height-lg">What's the same and what's different? Compare these two NASA flagship missions.</p><div class="margin-top-2"><a href="https://science.nasa.gov/mission/hubble/observatory/hubble-vs-webb/" target="_self" class="button-primary button-primary-md link-external-false"><span role="textbox" aria-multiline="true" aria-label="Write button text here" class="line-height-alt-1" style="white-space: pre-wrap; min-width: 1px;">Read More</span><svg viewBox="0 0 32 32" fill="none" xmlns="http://www.w3.org/2000/svg"><circle class="button-primary-circle" cx="16" cy="16" r="16"></circle><path d="M8 16.956h12.604l-3.844 4.106 1.252 1.338L24 16l-5.988-6.4-1.252 1.338 3.844 4.106H8v1.912z" class="color-spacesuit-white"></path></svg></a></div></div></div></div><div class="hds-card-custom hds-card color-carbon-black display-flex flex-column margin-bottom-5 "><div class="hds-card-inner"><div class="hds-card-thumbnail hds-card-hover-zoom-image margin-bottom-2 bg-carbon-black"><figure class="hds-media-background  "><img width="936" height="1024" src="https://science.nasa.gov/wp-content/uploads/2023/04/hubble-v838mon-heic0405a-jpg.webp?w=936" class="attachment-large size-large" alt="Hubble view of an expanding halo of light around star V838 Monocerotis. Center of the ball-like cloud holds a bright star surrounded by red gas. The outer region of the &quot;ball&quot; is a tan color dotted with stars. Black background dotted with stars." style="transform: scale(1); transform-origin: 50% 50%; object-position: 50% 50%; object-fit: cover;" block_context="nasa-block" loading="lazy" decoding="async" srcset="https://science.nasa.gov/wp-content/uploads/2023/04/hubble-v838mon-heic0405a-jpg.webp 2238w, https://science.nasa.gov/wp-content/uploads/2023/04/hubble-v838mon-heic0405a-jpg.webp?resize=274,300 274w, https://science.nasa.gov/wp-content/uploads/2023/04/hubble-v838mon-heic0405a-jpg.webp?resize=768,840 768w, https://science.nasa.gov/wp-content/uploads/2023/04/hubble-v838mon-heic0405a-jpg.webp?resize=936,1024 936w, https://science.nasa.gov/wp-content/uploads/2023/04/hubble-v838mon-heic0405a-jpg.webp?resize=1404,1536 1404w, https://science.nasa.gov/wp-content/uploads/2023/04/hubble-v838mon-heic0405a-jpg.webp?resize=1872,2048 1872w, https://science.nasa.gov/wp-content/uploads/2023/04/hubble-v838mon-heic0405a-jpg.webp?resize=366,400 366w, https://science.nasa.gov/wp-content/uploads/2023/04/hubble-v838mon-heic0405a-jpg.webp?resize=549,600 549w, https://science.nasa.gov/wp-content/uploads/2023/04/hubble-v838mon-heic0405a-jpg.webp?resize=823,900 823w, https://science.nasa.gov/wp-content/uploads/2023/04/hubble-v838mon-heic0405a-jpg.webp?resize=1097,1200 1097w, https://science.nasa.gov/wp-content/uploads/2023/04/hubble-v838mon-heic0405a-jpg.webp?resize=1828,2000 1828w" sizes="auto, (max-width: 936px) 100vw, 936px" /></figure></div><div class="padding-right-0"><div class="margin-bottom-1"><h3 class="heading-18">Hubble Science Highlights</h3></div><p class="margin-top-0 line-height-lg">Hubble has affected every area of astronomy. Its most notable scientific discoveries reflect the broad range of research and the breakthroughs it has achieved.</p><div class="margin-top-2"><a href="https://science.nasa.gov/mission/hubble/science/science-highlights/" target="_self" class="button-primary button-primary-md link-external-false"><span role="textbox" aria-multiline="true" aria-label="Write button text here" class="line-height-alt-1" style="white-space: pre-wrap; min-width: 1px;">Read More</span><svg viewBox="0 0 32 32" fill="none" xmlns="http://www.w3.org/2000/svg"><circle class="button-primary-circle" cx="16" cy="16" r="16"></circle><path d="M8 16.956h12.604l-3.844 4.106 1.252 1.338L24 16l-5.988-6.4-1.252 1.338 3.844 4.106H8v1.912z" class="color-spacesuit-white"></path></svg></a></div></div></div></div><div class="hds-card-custom hds-card color-carbon-black display-flex flex-column margin-bottom-5 "><div class="hds-card-inner"><div class="hds-card-thumbnail hds-card-hover-zoom-image margin-bottom-2 bg-carbon-black"><figure class="hds-media-background  "><img width="1024" height="1024" src="https://science.nasa.gov/wp-content/uploads/2023/04/hubble-nebula-crab-nebula-display-1-jpg.webp?w=1024" class="attachment-large size-large" alt="Hubble Nebula - Crab Nebula" style="transform: scale(1); transform-origin: 50% 50%; object-position: 50% 50%; object-fit: cover;" block_context="nasa-block" loading="lazy" decoding="async" srcset="https://science.nasa.gov/wp-content/uploads/2023/04/hubble-nebula-crab-nebula-display-1-jpg.webp 1120w, https://science.nasa.gov/wp-content/uploads/2023/04/hubble-nebula-crab-nebula-display-1-jpg.webp?resize=150,150 150w, https://science.nasa.gov/wp-content/uploads/2023/04/hubble-nebula-crab-nebula-display-1-jpg.webp?resize=300,300 300w, https://science.nasa.gov/wp-content/uploads/2023/04/hubble-nebula-crab-nebula-display-1-jpg.webp?resize=768,768 768w, https://science.nasa.gov/wp-content/uploads/2023/04/hubble-nebula-crab-nebula-display-1-jpg.webp?resize=1024,1024 1024w, https://science.nasa.gov/wp-content/uploads/2023/04/hubble-nebula-crab-nebula-display-1-jpg.webp?resize=50,50 50w, https://science.nasa.gov/wp-content/uploads/2023/04/hubble-nebula-crab-nebula-display-1-jpg.webp?resize=100,100 100w, https://science.nasa.gov/wp-content/uploads/2023/04/hubble-nebula-crab-nebula-display-1-jpg.webp?resize=200,200 200w, https://science.nasa.gov/wp-content/uploads/2023/04/hubble-nebula-crab-nebula-display-1-jpg.webp?resize=400,400 400w, https://science.nasa.gov/wp-content/uploads/2023/04/hubble-nebula-crab-nebula-display-1-jpg.webp?resize=600,600 600w, https://science.nasa.gov/wp-content/uploads/2023/04/hubble-nebula-crab-nebula-display-1-jpg.webp?resize=900,900 900w" sizes="auto, (max-width: 1024px) 100vw, 1024px" /></figure></div><div class="padding-right-0"><div class="margin-bottom-1"><h3 class="heading-18">Explore the Night Sky</h3></div><p class="margin-top-0 line-height-lg">Your backyard telescope and binoculars may not have the capabilities of Hubble, but you can still see amazing objects. Compare what you see with the images Hubble has taken.</p><div class="margin-top-2"><a href="https://science.nasa.gov/mission/hubble/science/explore-the-night-sky/" target="_self" class="button-primary button-primary-md link-external-false"><span role="textbox" aria-multiline="true" aria-label="Write button text here" class="line-height-alt-1" style="white-space: pre-wrap; min-width: 1px;">Read More</span><svg viewBox="0 0 32 32" fill="none" xmlns="http://www.w3.org/2000/svg"><circle class="button-primary-circle" cx="16" cy="16" r="16"></circle><path d="M8 16.956h12.604l-3.844 4.106 1.252 1.338L24 16l-5.988-6.4-1.252 1.338 3.844 4.106H8v1.912z" class="color-spacesuit-white"></path></svg></a></div></div></div></div><div class="hds-card-custom hds-card color-carbon-black display-flex flex-column margin-bottom-5 "><div class="hds-card-inner"><div class="hds-card-thumbnail hds-card-hover-zoom-image margin-bottom-2 bg-carbon-black"><figure class="hds-media-background  "><img width="1024" height="1024" src="https://science.nasa.gov/wp-content/uploads/2023/04/1-hst_overview-2019-1.png?w=1024" class="attachment-large size-large" alt="Hubble Space Telescope" style="transform: scale(1); transform-origin: 50% 50%; object-position: 50% 50%; object-fit: cover;" block_context="nasa-block" loading="lazy" decoding="async" srcset="https://science.nasa.gov/wp-content/uploads/2023/04/1-hst_overview-2019-1.png 3000w, https://science.nasa.gov/wp-content/uploads/2023/04/1-hst_overview-2019-1.png?resize=150,150 150w, https://science.nasa.gov/wp-content/uploads/2023/04/1-hst_overview-2019-1.png?resize=300,300 300w, https://science.nasa.gov/wp-content/uploads/2023/04/1-hst_overview-2019-1.png?resize=768,768 768w, https://science.nasa.gov/wp-content/uploads/2023/04/1-hst_overview-2019-1.png?resize=1024,1024 1024w, https://science.nasa.gov/wp-content/uploads/2023/04/1-hst_overview-2019-1.png?resize=1536,1536 1536w, https://science.nasa.gov/wp-content/uploads/2023/04/1-hst_overview-2019-1.png?resize=2048,2048 2048w, https://science.nasa.gov/wp-content/uploads/2023/04/1-hst_overview-2019-1.png?resize=50,50 50w, https://science.nasa.gov/wp-content/uploads/2023/04/1-hst_overview-2019-1.png?resize=100,100 100w, https://science.nasa.gov/wp-content/uploads/2023/04/1-hst_overview-2019-1.png?resize=200,200 200w, https://science.nasa.gov/wp-content/uploads/2023/04/1-hst_overview-2019-1.png?resize=400,400 400w, https://science.nasa.gov/wp-content/uploads/2023/04/1-hst_overview-2019-1.png?resize=600,600 600w, https://science.nasa.gov/wp-content/uploads/2023/04/1-hst_overview-2019-1.png?resize=900,900 900w, https://science.nasa.gov/wp-content/uploads/2023/04/1-hst_overview-2019-1.png?resize=1200,1200 1200w, https://science.nasa.gov/wp-content/uploads/2023/04/1-hst_overview-2019-1.png?resize=2000,2000 2000w" sizes="auto, (max-width: 1024px) 100vw, 1024px" /></figure></div><div class="padding-right-0"><div class="margin-bottom-1"><h3 class="heading-18">Hubble E-books</h3></div><p class="margin-top-0 line-height-lg">Investigate the mysteries of the universe with Hubble. Learn Hubble's history. E-books dive deeper into Hubble discoveries and more.</p><div class="margin-top-2"><a href="https://science.nasa.gov/mission/hubble/multimedia/e-books/" target="_self" class="button-primary button-primary-md link-external-false"><span role="textbox" aria-multiline="true" aria-label="Write button text here" class="line-height-alt-1" style="white-space: pre-wrap; min-width: 1px;">Read More</span><svg viewBox="0 0 32 32" fill="none" xmlns="http://www.w3.org/2000/svg"><circle class="button-primary-circle" cx="16" cy="16" r="16"></circle><path d="M8 16.956h12.604l-3.844 4.106 1.252 1.338L24 16l-5.988-6.4-1.252 1.338 3.844 4.106H8v1.912z" class="color-spacesuit-white"></path></svg></a></div></div></div></div>			</div>
							<button class="hds-carousel-nav-arrow hds-carousel-arrow-next margin-right-0">
